Ekiti State Government has warned three communities fighting over boundaries to stay off disputed areas until the matter is resolved. Three communities of Ipoti Ekiti, Ejiyan Ekiti and Owatedo Ekiti are fighting over boundaries. The Deputy Governor in a statement on Thursday by his Special Assistant (Media), Odunayo Ogunmola, said the state government still stands by its directive that the three towns should refrain from erecting any structure or carrying out any development on their disputed boundaries until the conclusion of demarcation of the boundaries. 2023 Presidency: Sanwo-Olu Urges APC Leaders To Unite For Tinubu Buhari Consulting Over Re-Amended Electoral Bill — Aide The government urged the communities to wait for the outcome of the report of the technical committee of the State Boundary Commission working on the demarcation of the boundaries. It warned them against taking any step that could lead to the breakdown of law and order in the area. Three towns to toe the line of peace and cooperate with the state government to ensure an amicable resolution of the boundary dispute in the interest of peace and tranquillity. It stressed that taking an action on the land in dispute boundaries of the three communities negates the agreement reached during a meeting held by the stakeholders in his office and runs contrary to the directive not to carry out any activity on the disputed land. It said: “Our directive that no individual, groups or towns should carry out economic or social activities along the disputed boundaries among the three towns still stands. POLL “Government is determined to ensure a peaceful resolution of the dispute and the Technical Committee has been given the mandate to carry out the proper demarcation of the boundaries and submit its report. “The communities must wait for the committee to conclude its assignment. The full wrath of the law shall be visited on any individual or group in any of the towns that go against the directive.”